==Starting out==
===Talking to Lazim===
* '''Lazim:''' Ah, an adventurer. Could you spare some of your time to help me?
* '''Player:''' Why, what's the matter?
* '''Lazim:''' It's a sorry tale. I was once an accomplished sculptor, you see.
* '''Lazim:''' I made statues for the kings, queens and rulers of Gielinor. But then there was the accident...
* '''Lazim:''' After that, I could never hold a chisel again.
* '''Lazim:''' But I have been struck by my muse while travelling the desert, and want nothing more than to build a statue in this area.
* '''Lazim:''' The desert's plain and full of sand, and needs more decoration.
* '''Player:''' So, what would you need my help with?
* '''Lazim:''' As I said, I can't hold a chisel, but I can guide you in crafting the statue for me.
* '''Lazim:''' I'd need you to quarry the stone for it, as well.
* '''Lazim:''' Well, will you help me with my art?
* {{topt|Of course!}}
** '''Player:''' Of course!
** '''Player:''' You'll have to explain it to me as you go along, but count me in.
** '''Lazim:''' Excellent.
** '''Player:''' What should I be doing to make your statue?
** '''Lazim:''' There is a stone quarry nearby; I require several blocks of sandstone in order to make the statue.
** '''Lazim:''' Each of these blocks should be around... well, let's say thirty two kilograms for the first one.
** '''Player:''' I can't mine a block that big!
** '''Lazim:''' Well, then, bring me enough smaller blocks to make thirty two kilograms, and I will deal with it.
** {{topt|So, how much do different blocks of sandstone weigh?}}
*** '''Player:''' So, how much do different blocks of sandstone weigh?
*** '''Lazim:''' From what the last adventurer told me, there are tiny blocks that weigh 1 kg, small blocks that weigh 2 kg, and medium-sized blocks that weigh 5 kg.
*** '''Lazim:''' There are also large blocks that weigh 10 kg, but I doubt a weedy adventurer like you could even carry one, let alone mine one cleanly.
*** '''Lazim:''' Apparently, the more skilled you are at mining, the larger the blocks you can chip off the rock.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Okay, I'll get on with it.}}
*** '''Player:''' Okay, I'll get on with it.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I don't know, that sounds like a lot of work.}}
** '''Player:''' I don't know, that sounds like a lot of work.
** '''Lazim:''' All true art requires work.
** {{tact|end}}

