===Talking to Lazim after chiseling the statue===
* '''Lazim:''' It shouldn't have taken this long... did I miscalculate?
* '''Lazim:''' Ah, adventurer. As you can see, the statue is nearly complete. All it needs is a head.
* '''Lazim:''' The head should be made out of granite, which you can find in that quarry nearby.
* '''Lazim:''' As for whose head... well, perhaps I'll let you impose your own artistic vision on it.
* '''Lazim:''' Whose head do you think should be on the statue?
* {{topt|I think it should have my head!}}
** '''Player:''' I think it should have my head!
** '''Lazim:''' Are you mad?
** '''Lazim:''' You'd start carving it, then you'd take a helmet off or change your hairstyle, and nobody would know who on Gielinor it was supposed to be!
** '''Lazim:''' Statues are far more permanent than you adventurers and your fashions.
** '''Player:''' So I can't put my head on the statue?
** '''Lazim:''' No. Now choose something sensible.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|I think it should have your head.}}
** '''Player:''' I think it should have your head.
** '''Player:''' After all, it's your statue.
** '''Lazim:''' Why, that's very generous of you, adventurer.
** '''Lazim:''' Are you hoping for a bigger reward for saying that?
** '''Player:''' Er, maybe.
** '''Lazim:''' Wonderful. Well, at least you have me here for reference.
** '''Lazim:''' Now, go and find a suitable block of granite and make that head.
** '''Lazim:''' And do try to remember which one it is you're carving.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I think it should have a god's head.}}
